draw(A--B--C--cycle);

draw(A--D);

draw(A--E,dashed);

label("$A$", A, N);

label("$B$", B, W);

label("$C$", C, SE);

label("$D$", D, SW);

label("$E$", E, S);

dot("$O$", O, dir(0));

[/asy]

ref_solution:
Since triangle $ACD$ is right, $\angle CAD = 90^\circ - \angle ACD = 90^\circ - 50^\circ = 40^\circ$.

[asy]
